<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="id_lgintestine_digt"><title>tutor</title><page id="e28b7fc05cf54354bd9af29e0b305c0f"><question id="q1"><body><p id="ac0478cec385c40b98377d7b5eae51c1f">The bacterial degradation of chyme components occurs where?</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="ff6623fded8f43c684672a77f9b2c505" labels="false"><choice value="A">In the lumen</choice><choice value="B">In the mucosa</choice><choice value="C">In the Muscularis externa</choice><choice value="D">In the blood stream</choice></multiple_choice><part id="bc23fd9ef6d445eb8d89c84a8f84926c"><skillref idref="id_lgintestine_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="10"><feedback><p id="aeefc1498831344d998af36e0304642d8">Correct. The bacterial flora of the lumen will digest some of the nutrients left in the chyme.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="af64ffc3dbce14a5a8d81e607133fd573">Incorrect. The mucosa secretes mucus and is responsible for absorption.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab0c3a3ea2b5c447b8378390e663620a8">Incorrect. The muscularis externa is responsible for muscle contractions that move the feces.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab32b890dddf64ca5a2cc0149ad11f3ea">Incorrect. Bacteria in the blood would cause a systemic reaction that could result in illness.</p></feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
